channel.title: RSPS General Help
channel.description: Hey everyone I wanted to know if someone could graciously offer a small piece of their time to help me getting my blank 317 server online and running so my friends can join. I am inexperienced with runescape private servers but I do have some knowledge in Java. I have tried following various tutorials and watched multiple youtube videos but there is nothing like a person sitting down and explaining to you what actually needs to happen. I understand if no one wants to attempt, but I thought I'd take a shot in the dark. Thank you all and have a great day.

Well if you’re portforwarded and you have an IP and a server, all you need to do is change the IP in the client, compile, and send it to your friends. If they’re inexperienced you can make it a jar file so all they have to do is click it.
